    "rationale": "This reaction shows the oxidation of a simple, acyclic primary alcohol (1-pentanol) to the corresponding aldehyde (pentanal) using dimethyl sulfoxide (DMSO) and a carbodiimide (N,N'-dicyclohexylcarbodiimide, DCC), which are the defining reagents for the Pfitzner-Moffatt oxidation. The substrate is simple and avoids reactive functional groups that could cause collisions with other named reactions.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "The substrate is a simple primary alcohol, avoiding complex structures, aromatic rings, or additional functional groups that could trigger other named reaction queries. The explicit inclusion of DMSO and a carbodiimide (DCC) as reagents strongly anchors this example to activated-DMSO oxidations, specifically the Pfitzner-Moffatt variant, distinguishing it from other oxidation methods (e.g., Swern, Corey-Kim, Dess-Martin)."
